The paper deals with the problem of automatically extracting important content elements from business documents, which is a task that falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning models such as BERT, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of image processing techniques for property lease agreements, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
